  "title": "Trading Contracts Executive (Oil & Gas MNC)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client is a Trading MNC, one of the leading players in the Oil & Gas sector. Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a Contract Analyst to be part of their Contract team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the Town – easily accessible.</strong><br /></p><p>The Duties of Contract Analyst:</p><ul><li>Review, draft, negotiate, and issue sale and purchase contracts to support the company’s trading operations.</li><li>Ensure all contracts comply with corporate policies, signatory requirements, and internal procedures.</li><li>Assess contractual terms to safeguard the company’s legal and commercial interests, manage risks, and enhance commercial outcomes.</li><li>Oversee contract administration and maintain adherence to established documentation and process standards.</li><li>Provide regular updates to the Legal team on contract progress, key issues, and risk escalations, and support other contract-related tasks as required.</li></ul><p>Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Min Degree in Law or other business-related field</li><li>3 years of experience in handling trading contracts </li></ul><p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click <strong>APPLY NOW</strong> or email an updated copy of your resume / cv.</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</p><ul><li><strong>Email Address: jobs@recruitpedia.sg</strong></li><li>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</li><li>EA License No. 19C9682</li><li>EA Reg. No. R2198636 (Oh Puey Xin)</li></ul>",
